{
  "texts": [
    "GPT, on the other hand, yields average predictions that are much more distant from average WVS answers, with nEMD ranging from.143 to.332.",
    "Results are similar when considering variable-wise disaggregated averages (eg.",
    "averaging over women and men).",
    "Comparing answer distributions at the fine-grained subpopulation level gives a more detailed picture.",
    "Considering all 687 subpopulations and 4 outcome variables together, the distance between the predictions of the three LLMs and the survey responses is usually high."
  ]
}